The paper deals with image super-resolution, which is a common topic in computer vision (cs.CV). The use of deep learning techniques such as generative adversarial networks (GANs) and deep image matting also suggests a focus on artificial intelligence (cs.AI) and machine learning (cs.LG). The use of text images and document images suggests a potential focus on information retrieval (cs.IR) and natural language processing (cs.CL).
